description: The fund seeks to achieve its investment goal by allocating its assets across two underlying "alternative" investment strategies, which represent top-down and bottom-up approaches to capturing factor-based risk premia. Through the two strategies, it may invest in or obtain exposure to: (i) equity securities (which may include common stocks and preferred stocks), (ii) debt securities (which may include bonds, notes, debentures, banker's acceptances and commercial paper), (iii) commodity-linked derivative instruments and (iv) currency-related derivative instruments.
name: Franklin Systematic Style Premia ETF
